bsite%20owners%20and%20other%20content%20companies%20would%20be%20able%20to%20block%20bot%20crawlers%20from%20collecting%20their%20data%20for%20use%20in%20AI%20model%20training%20and%20AI%20model%20outputs%20%E2%80%94%20while%20still%20approving%20access%20for%20traditional%20search%20engines%20that%20send%20traffic%20to%20the%20original%20sources%20of%20information%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20definition%20centers%20on%20search%20engines.%20The%20IETF%20working%20document%20describes%20a%20search%20engine%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bapplication%20that%20directs%20users%20to%20the%20location%20from%20which%20the%20assets%20were%20retrieved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%2C%20under%20these%20emerging%20new%20internet%20standards%2C%20search%20engines%20would%20have%20to%20generate%20results%20that%20send%20users%20to%20the%20original%20sources%20of%20information%20to%20be%20considered%20truly%20a%20search%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20different%20from%20how%20search%20has%20been%20evolving%20recently.%20Google%20added%20AI%20Overviews%20and%20AI%20Mode%20to%20its%20search%20engine%20this%20year.%20These%20new%20features%20use%20website%20content%20for%20free%20to%20answer%20user%20questions%20directly%2C%20and%20this%20can%20send%20less%20traffic%20to%20the%20original%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294ee5a69-a527-447d-ab1e-cddfffe6ae25%5C%22%3EAI%20answer%20engines%20hit%20traffic%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20Pew%20research%20found%20that%20users%20who%20encountered%20an%20AI%20summary%20clicked%20on%20a%20traditional%20search%20result%20link%20only%208%25%20of%20the%20time.%20Those%20who%20did%20not%20encounter%20an%20AI%20summary%20clicked%20through%2015%25%20of%20the%20time.%20And%20Google%20users%20who%20saw%20an%20AI%20summary%20rarely%20clicked%20on%20a%20link%20in%20the%20summary%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20just%201%25%20of%20the%20time.%20Google%20has%20questioned%20the%20methodology%20of%20this%20study%2C%20although%20other%20studies%2