%20the%20website%20and%20viewed%2010%25%20fewer%20pages%20than%20the%20average%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20new%20IETF%20standards.%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20it%20is%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20until%20they%20are%20forced%20to%20break%20out%20the%20Google%20search%20bot%20from%20their%20other%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20Dicker%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20point%20we%20would%20look%20to%20block%20every%20Google%20bot%20we%20can%2C%20other%20than%20the%20one%20specifically%20sent%20out%20for%20search.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229f4497ef-98c1-4085-8ab7-896d47d5f32c%5C%22%3ECan%20you%20treat%20AI%20differently%20from%20search%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20emails%20to%20the%20IETF%20working%20group%2C%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20other%20big%20tech%20companies%20have%20argued%20that%20it's%20hard%20to%20separate%20search%20engines%20from%20AI%20because%20the%20two%20technologies%20have%20become%20so%20intertwined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20very%20many%20highly%20problematic%20areas%20in%20the%20document%2C%26quot%3B%20Krishna%20Madhavan%2C%20a%20principal%20product%20manager%20for%20Microsoft%20AI%20and%20the%20Bing%20web%20data%20platform%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20the%20IETF%20working%20group%20on%20August%2013.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModern%20search%20systems%20rely%20heavily%20on%20AI%2C%20even%20for%20basic%20rankings%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20another%20email%20on%20August%204.%20%26quot%3B%E2%80%AFAttempting%20to%20isolate%20'search'%20as%20a%20distinct%2C%20opt-out%20category%20ignores%20this%20integration%20and%20creates%20a%20false%20dichotomy%20that%20is%20neither%20meaningful%20nor%20enforceable%2C%26quot%3B%20Madhavan%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20July%2C%C2%A0Google%20copyright%20lawyer%20Caleb%20Donaldson%20warned%20that%20the%20company%20could%20drop%20websites%20from%20Search%20because%20the%20IETF%20definitions%20are%20confusing%20and%20could%20leave%20site%20owners%20opting%20out%20of%20broader%20automated%20bot%20crawling%20by%20accident.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20meaningful%20distinction%20between%20'AI%20Use'%20and%20'Search'%20given%20all%20of%20Search%20runs%20on%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20the%20IETF%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20from%20Amazon%20and%20OpenAI%20concurred%20with%20Donaldson%20in%20other%20emails%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0OpenAI's%20lawyer%20even%20insinuated%20that%20the%20IETF's%20guidelines%20could%20be%20cited%20by%20regulators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20also%20acknowledge%2C%20not%20ignore%2C%20the%20legal%20overhang%3A%20once%20published%2C%20this%20vocabulary%20will%20be%20cited%20by%20regulators%20and%20others%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0Esther%20Tetruashvily%2C%20an%20AI%20Standards%20Specialist%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20asked%20Google%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20for%20comment.%20Microsoft%20declined%20to%20comment.%20OpenAI%20said%20its%20stance%20is%20represented%20by%20Tetruashvily's%20emails%20to%20the%20IETF%2C%20while%20Google%20said%20the%20views%20expressed%20by%20the%20Google%20executives%20and%20lawyers%20in%20the%20IETF%20group%20are%20not%20%26quot%3Bofficial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20models%20have%20been%20core%20to%20how%20Search%20works%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20helping%20surface%20relevant%20sites%20and%20driving%20traffic%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Google%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnlike%20many%20others%2C%20we%20respect%20the%20choices%20that%20sites%20make%20through%20robots.txt%2C%20and%20we%20also%20provide%20snippet%20controls%20that%20let%20publishers%20opt%20out%20of%20having%20their%20content%20appear%20in%20Search%20features%20like%20AI%20Overviews.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229cea4043-7548-44e5-91a2-eac9fe6c8a90%5C%22%3EA%C2%A0'carve-out'%20for%20Search%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn