7B%22title%22%3A%22Welcome%20to%20the%20Great%20Lock%20In%3A%20'No%20excuses%2C%20just%20grind.'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20locks%20and%20self%20care%20imagery%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bf33a8f9db348adc0b0fac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20fall%2C%20buckos.%20Are%20you%20going%20to%20rot%20your%20way%20through%20December%2C%20or%20are%20you%20locking%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20social%20media%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20Lock%20In%26quot%3B%20has%20begun.%20From%20September%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20participants%20say%20they%20are%20walking%20five%20miles%20every%20day%20in%20weighted%20vests.%20They're%20sleeping%20eight%20hours%20a%20night.%20They're%20drinking%20several%20liters%20of%20water%20a%20day.%20They're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-delete-instagram-social-media-vacation-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeactivating%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20not%20before%20posting%20their%20lengthy%20lists%20on%20how%20to%20lock%20in%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20it%20means%20to%20go%20locked-in%20mode%20varies%20wildly%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20a%20lock-in%20for%20every%20key%2C%20it%20seems.%20The%20Great%20Lock%20In%20can%20include%20tackling%20financial%20goals%2C%20finding%20love%2C%20building%20community%2C%20and%2C%20perhaps%20more%20than%20anything%2C%20achieving%20maximum%20wellness.%20For%20women%20on%20TikTok%2C%20it's%20a%20time%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbenefits-of-journaling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejournal%20and%20set%20intentions%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20self-improvement%3B%20for%20men%20on%20X%2C%20it's%20about%20maxing%20out%20on%20protein%2C%20skipping%20sugar%2C%20and%20taking%20cold%20showers.%20%26quot%3BNo%20excuses%2C%20just%20grind%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20rule%20posted%20to%20X%20states.%20In%20a%20culture%20obsessed%20with%20improvement%2C%20productivity%20hacks%2C%20and%20ideal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-obessesion-morning-routines-habits-productivity-masculinity-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emorning%20routines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20locking%20in%20is%20the%20latest%20cult%20of%20self-upgrade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoodbye%20to%20the%20anti-work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-job-trend-tiktok-explained-defending-low-stress-work-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elazy%20girl%3C%2Fa%3E%20era%20or%20a%20summer%20of%20hedonism%2C%20where%20day%20drinking%20is%20followed%20by%20nightly%20doomscrolling%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrain-rot-summer-coldplaygate-jet2holidays-monoculture-movies-songs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrain%20rot%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20AI%20slop.%20To%20close%20out%20a%20year%20marked%20by%20a%20herky-jerky%20economy%2C%20doom%20and%20gloom%20news%20cycles%2C%20and%20an%20increasing%20focus%20on%20the%20loneliness%20epidemic%2C%20people%20are%20committing%20to%20a%20121-day-long%20mindful%2C%20self%20improvement%20journey%20that's%20part-%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F75-hard-tiktok-challenge-safe-mental-toughness-weight-loss-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%20Hard%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20part-preamble%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-science-backed-new-years-resolutions-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20Year's%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20part%20back-to-school%20energy%20(nostalgically%20so%20for%20those%20who%20graduated%20long%20ago)%2C%20and%20ultimately%20the%20latest%20iteration%20of%20optimization%20culture.%20Whatever%20end%20game%20people%20have%20in%20mind%2C%20the%20process%20is%20a%20way%20to%20take%20control%20back%20from%20a%20chaotic%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKadie%20Glenn%20is%20among%20the%20locked-in%20corps.%20The%2028-year-old%20London-based%20personal%20consultant%20had%20a%20bad%20start%20to%20her%202025.%20She%20tells%20me%20she%20went%20through%20a%20breakup%20and%20moved%2C%20and%20her%20aspirational%20goals%20for%20the%20year%20were%20hard%20to%20reach.%20Instead%2C%20Glenn%20says%2C%20she's%20focusing%20on%20smaller%20changes%20across%20shorter%20chunks%20of%20time%2C%20first%20by%20breaking%20down%20her%20life%20into%20certain%20areas%2C%20like%20health%2C%20career%2C%20or%20relationships%2C%20and%20then%20focusing%20on%20the%20areas%20that%20need%20the%20most%20work%20rather%20than%20a%20full%20overhaul%20of%20her%20life.%20Right%20now%2C%20her%20big%20goal%20to%20run%20a%20half%20marathon%20in%20early%202026%2C%20but%20she's%20starting%20with%20committing%20to%20regular%20runs%20and%20scaling%20up%20for%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20just%20arrived%20at%20that%20point%20wanting%20to%20refuel%2C%20wanting%20to%20get%20something%20out%20of%202025%20other%20than%20what%20it%20has%20been%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Glenn%2C%20who%20posted%20about%20the%20Great%20Lock%20In%20and%20then%20started%20Instagram%20chats%20for%20her%20followers%20to%20discuss%20their%20goals%20and%20team%20up.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20want%20to%20reframe%20the%20narrative.%20People%20want%20to%20start%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuccess%20for%20self-improvement%20campaigns%20is%20mixed.%20A%20YouGov%20poll%20found%20that%20in%202020%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20people%20in%20the%20US%20made%20New%20Year's%20resolutions%2C%20and%20around%20half%20kept%20some%20of%20their%20resolutions%2C%20while%20around%20a%20third%20stuck%20to%20them%20all.%20Swedish%20researchers%20found%20in%20a%202020%20study%20that%20New%20Year's%20resolutions%20that%20seek%20to%20approach%20a%20goal%20rather%20than%20avoid%20a%20habit%20(for%20example%2C%20starting%20a%20gym%20routine%20versus%20quitting%20sugary%20snacks)%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20successful%2C%20as%20do%20people%20who%20receive%20support%20in%20achieving%20their%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20Katy%20Milkman%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School%20reminds%20me%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20change%2C%20and%20you%20won't%20change%20at%20all%20if%20you%20don't%20at%20least%20start%20trying.%20Milkman%2C%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Change%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20the%20Great%20Lock%20In%20is%20an%20example%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfresh%20start%20effect.%26quot%3B%20It's%20the%20idea%20that%20a%20birthday%2C%20new%20year%2C%20or%20even%20the%20start%20to%20a%20new%20month%20or%20week%20can%20bring%20the%20potential%20to%20start%20new%20habits.%20And%20if%20the%20season%20of%20locking%20in%20seems%20arbitrarily%20tied%20to%20September%2C%20%26quot%3Bevery%20fresh%20start%20is%20socially%20constructed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20But%20those%20fresh%20starts%20can%20come%20when%20people%20feel%20stuck%20and%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20current%20version%20of%20their%20lives.%20%26quot%3BThe%20worse%20the%20old%20chapter%20was%2C%20the%20more%20you%20need%20the%20fresh%20start.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20strict%2075%20Hard%20program%20(a%20challenge%20pulled%20from%20a%202020%20self-help%20book%20of%20the%20same%20name%20that%20involves%20changing%20your%20diet%2C%20fitness%20regimen%2C%20and%20reading%20daily)%2C%20the%20Great%20Lock%20In%20is%20a%20grassroots%20social%20media%20movement%20that%20began%20bubbling%20up%20on%20social%20media%20in%20August.%20It's%20a%20continuation%20or%20rebrand%20of%20last%20year's%20Winter%20Arc%2C%20which%20last%20fall%20encouraged%20people%20to%20use%20chilly%20months%20to%20start%20chiseling%20away%20at%20the%20parts%20of%20themselves%20they%20didn't%20like%20and%20emerge%20as%20their%20best%20self.%20The%20Great%20Lock%20In%20also%20follows%20years%20of%20people%20%26quot%3Blocking%20in%26quot%3B%20and%20putting%20all%20of%20their%20energy%20onto%20various%20tasks%2C%20like%20studying%20or%20cleaning%2C%20as%20they%20arise.%20It's%20part%20of%20the%20grindset%20mentality%20focused%20on%20building%20wealth%20and%20success%2C%20a%20more%20personalized%20and%20flexible%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F996-work-culture-schedule-popular-in-china-explained-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E9-9-6%3C%2Fa%3E%20(working%20from%209%20a.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%20six%20days%20a%20week).%20In%20a%20world%20where%20distractions%20are%20ever%20present%20on%20our%20phones%2C%20a%20longer%20lock%20in%20period%20to%20tackle%20a%20range%20of%20goals%20is%20resonating%20with%20Gen%20Z%20%E2%80%94%20even%20for%20those%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fknowyourmeme.com%2Fmemes%2Fborn-to-dilly-dally-forced-to-lock-in%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborn%20to%20dilly%20dally%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20forced%20to%20lock%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERacha%20Yessouf%2C%20a%2026-year-old%20wellness%20content%20creator%20in%20London%2C%20has%20started%20working%20on%20what%20she%20deems%20the%20%26quot%3Bhot%20girl%20edition%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Great%20Lock%20In.%20Her%20self-imposed%20rules%20include%20waking%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%2C%20drinking%20lots%20of%20water%2C%20doing%20regular%20skin%20and%20hair%20care%2C%20eating%20lots%20of%20protein%2C%20and%20going%20to%20bed%20by%209%20p.m.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20about%20reinventing%20yourself%20in%20the%20way%20New%20Year's%20resolutions%20tend%20to%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Yessouf%20says%20(she%20was%20already%20working%20out%20and%20had%20a%20beauty%20regimen).%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20about%20focusing%20on%20consistency%20and%20going%20into%20the%20new%20year%20with%20the%20momentum%20already%20built%20instead%20of%20guilt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETatiana%20Forbes%20has%20three%20goals%20she's%20locking%20in%20on%3A%20decluttering%20her%20house%2C%20getting%20her%20Instagram%20account%20to%20100%2C000%20followers%2C%20and%20running%20two%20marathons%20this%20fall.%20The%2031-year-old%20Atlanta-based%20leadership%20development%20coach%20says%20she%20did%20the%2075%20Hard%20challenge%20previously%2C%20and%20the%20locking%20in%20movement%20feels%20like%20a%20way%20to%20wellness%20where%20%26quot%3Byou're%20creating%20your%20own%20rules%20and%20own%20journey%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20means%20tackling%20more%20than%20just%20diet%20and%20exercise.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20us%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcure-for-doomscrolling-shaming-your-friends-screentime-app-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaddicted%20to%20our%20phones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20are%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20new%20beauty%20standards%20that%20are%20pushed%20to%20us%20through%20the%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20challenge%20is%20giving%20you%20time%20to%20take%20your%20power%20back%20and%20focus%20on%20what%20you%20want%20to%20focus%20on%20and%20shut%20out%20the%20noise%20for%20a%20little%20bit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20challenges%20come%20and%20go.%20The%20Great%20Lock%20In%20might%20fade%20from%20FYPs%20before%20October%2C%20with%20lists%20of%20rules%20abandoned%20in%20notes%20apps%20on%20phones%20one%20by%20one.%20But%20for%20those%20who%20are%20really%20committed%20to%20lock%20in%2C%20there's%20never%20a%20better%20time%20to%20make%20a%20fresh%20start%20than%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%